&lt;p&gt;I am trying to print an integer in &lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JavaScript&quot; rel=&quot;noreferrer&quot;&gt;JavaScript&lt;/a&gt; with commas as thousands separators. For example, I want to show the number 1234567 as &quot;1,234,567&quot;. How would I go about doing this? &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is how I am doing it:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-js s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-javascript&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;numberWithCommas&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-params&quot;&gt;x&lt;/span&gt;) {
    x = x.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;toString&lt;/span&gt;();
    &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; pattern = &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-regexp&quot;&gt;/(-?\d+)(\d{3})/&lt;/span&gt;;
    &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; (pattern.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;test&lt;/span&gt;(x))
        x = x.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;replace&lt;/span&gt;(pattern, &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&quot;$1,$2&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
    &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; x;
}
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is there a simpler or more elegant way to do it? It would be nice if it works with floats also, but that is not necessary. It does not need to be locale-specific to decide between periods and commas. &lt;/p&gt;
